Doc# 20220027673 02/02/2022 10:22AM Page 1 of 3 Lucy Adame-Clark, Bexar County Clerk
SCANNED
REAL ESTATE LIEN NOTE
Date:
January 24th, 2022
Maker:
Hector Rodriguez And Suhail Rodriguez
Maker's Address:
902 Elk Horn
San Antonio, Texas 78218-8138
Payee:
TMT REVOCABLE TRUST
Payee's Address:
6938 Ashbrook
San Antonio, Texas 78239
Principal Amount:
$ 120,483.00
Annual Interest Rate on Unpaid Principal from Date:
0 %
Annual Interest Rate on Unpaid Amounts:
18%
Term of Payment: This note shall be due and payable in monthly installment of $ 669.00 or
more each, payable on the 1st day of each and every calendar month; beginning March 181,
2022 and sums due hereunder shall be due and payable in full. Payments shall be applied first
to accrued Interest and the balance to the reduction of principal. Maker agrees to pay a late
charge of 8 % upon any amount received more than five (5) days in arrears to cover the extra
expense involved in handling delinquent payment. Maker agrees to pay a $ 35.00 charge for
returned checks. Maker may prepay all or any part of this note at any time without penalty. Any
prepayments are to be applied to the payment of the installments of principal of last maturing.
Security for Payment:
Lot 70, Block 18, City Block 5073, Camelot Townhouse Subdivision. Unit 33-B, an addition in
Bexar County, Texas, according to map or plat thereof, recorded in volume 8800, Page 192,
Deed and Plat Records of Bexar county, Texas. Address known as 7801 Broadwick, San
Antonio, Texas, Bexar County 78239
If Maker defaults in the payment of this note or the performance of any obligation in any
instrument securing or collateral to it, and the default continues after Payee gives Maker notice
of the default and time within which it must be cured, as may be required by law or by written
agreement, then Payee may declare the unpaid principal balance and earned interest on this
note immediately due. Maker and each surety, endorser and guarantor waive all demands for
payment, presentations for payment, notices of intention to accelerate maturity, notices of
acceleration of maturity, protests and notices, to the extent permitted by law.
If this note or any instrument securing or collateral to it is given to an attorney for
collection or enforcement, or if suit is brought for collection or enforcement, or if it collected or
enforce through probate, bankruptcy, or other judicial proceeding, then Maker shall pay Payee
all cost of collection and enforcement, including reasonable attorneys fees and court costs, in
addition to other amounts due. Reasonable attorney's fees shall be 10% of all amounts due
unless either party pleads otherwise.
